subject: p11413236
Findings: Lung volumes are low, leading to crowding of the bronchovascular structures. There is no evidence of focal consolidation, pleural effusion, pneumothorax, or frank pulmonary edema. The heart remains moderately enlarged, although this is accentuated by AP technique and low lung volumes. Calcified AP window node is again noted. A right-sided Port-A-Cath terminates within the upper-mid SVC, unchanged in position from the prior exam.
Impression: Low lung volumes without evidence for acute cardiopulmonary process.
